module.exports = [
  [85, "Cultural Diversity in a Globalized World", "文化", 2,
"Cultural diversity, the variety of cultural expressions and practices that characterize different groups of people, faces both opportunities and threats in an increasingly globalized world. While globalization facilitates the exchange of ideas and traditions, it also risks homogenizing cultures and eroding local identities.\n\nThe United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization estimates that a language disappears approximately every two weeks. With each language loss, unique knowledge systems, oral traditions, and ways of understanding the world vanish. Of the approximately 7,000 languages spoken today, nearly half are at risk of extinction by the end of this century.\n\nCultural homogenization, driven by the dominance of certain languages and media, poses a significant threat. English has become the global language of business and the internet, while Western media and entertainment shape cultural preferences worldwide. This can marginalize local traditions and create pressure to conform to dominant cultural norms.\n\nHowever, globalization also offers tools for cultural preservation and promotion. Digital technologies enable communities to document and share their cultural heritage. Social media platforms allow minority cultures to reach global audiences. Cultural tourism can provide economic incentives for maintaining traditional practices. The challenge lies in harnessing the benefits of global connectivity while preserving the rich tapestry of human cultural diversity.",
"文化多样性在日益全球化的世界中既面临机遇也面临威胁。虽然全球化促进了思想和传统的交流，但也有同质化文化和侵蚀地方身份的风险。\n\n联合国教科文组织估计大约每两周就有一种语言消失。随着每种语言的消失，独特的知识体系、口头传统和理解世界的方式也随之消失。在目前约7000种语言中，近一半面临本世纪末灭绝的风险。\n\n文化同质化是一个重大威胁。英语已成为全球商业和互联网语言，而西方媒体和娱乐塑造了全球文化偏好。\n\n然而，全球化也提供了文化保存和推广的工具。数字技术使社区能够记录和分享其文化遗产。社交媒体平台允许少数文化接触全球受众。",
338,
[["How often does a language disappear according to UNESCO?","Every year","Approximately every two weeks","Every month","Every decade","B","文章指出大约每两周就有一种语言消失。"],["How many languages are spoken today?","About 1,000","About 3,000","About 7,000","About 10,000","C","文章指出目前约7000种语言。"],["What percentage of languages are at risk of extinction by the end of this century?","About 10%","About 25%","Nearly half","About 90%","C","文章指出近一半语言面临本世纪末灭绝的风险。"],["The word 'homogenizing' most likely means:","Making diverse and different","Making uniform or similar","Destroying completely","Protecting carefully","B","'homogenizing'意为'同质化'，即使变得相似或统一。"]]],

  [86, "The Preservation of Cultural Heritage", "文化", 2,
"Cultural heritage encompasses the tangible and intangible artifacts, traditions, and practices that are passed down from generation to generation. From ancient monuments and historical documents to traditional crafts and oral histories, cultural heritage provides communities with a sense of identity and continuity.\n\nTangible cultural heritage includes physical sites and objects such as temples, paintings, and archaeological artifacts. Many of these treasures face threats from natural disasters, armed conflict, urban development, and environmental degradation. The destruction of cultural sites during conflicts, such as the ancient city of Palmyra in Syria, represents an irreplaceable loss to humanity.\n\nIntangible cultural heritage includes living expressions such as oral traditions, performing arts, social practices, and traditional knowledge. Safeguarding intangible heritage is particularly challenging because it exists in the practices and memories of people rather than in physical objects. When practitioners die without passing on their knowledge, these traditions can be lost forever.\n\nInternational efforts to protect cultural heritage include the UNESCO World Heritage Convention, which designates sites of outstanding universal value for protection. Digital preservation technologies are creating virtual archives of threatened sites and practices. Community-based approaches that empower local people to preserve their own heritage are increasingly recognized as the most sustainable strategies.",
"文化遗产包括代代相传的有形和无形的人造物、传统和实践。从古代纪念碑和历史文献到传统工艺和口述历史，文化遗产为社区提供了身份认同和延续感。\n\n有形文化遗产包括寺庙、绘画和考古文物等物理场所和物品。其中许多珍品面临自然灾害、武装冲突、城市开发和环境退化的威胁。\n\n无形文化遗产包括口头传统、表演艺术、社会习俗和传统知识等活态表达。保护无形遗产特别具有挑战性。\n\n保护文化遗产的国际努力包括联合国教科文组织世界遗产公约。数字保存技术正在创建受威胁遗址和实践的虚拟档案。",
338,
[["What does tangible cultural heritage include?","Only oral traditions","Physical sites and objects such as temples, paintings, and artifacts","Only music and dance","Only digital files","B","文章指出有形文化遗产包括物理场所和物品。"],["What makes safeguarding intangible heritage particularly challenging?","It is too expensive","It exists in the practices and memories of people rather than physical objects","It is not important","There are too many laws protecting it","B","文章指出无形遗产存在于人的实践和记忆中而非物理物品中，这使其保护特别具有挑战。"],["What international effort protects cultural heritage?","The World Bank","The UNESCO World Heritage Convention","The IMF","The G7","B","文章指出联合国教科文组织世界遗产公约指定具有突出普遍价值的遗址进行保护。"],["The word 'irreplaceable' most likely means:","Easy to replace","Cannot be replaced if lost","Not important","Very common","B","'irreplaceable'意为'不可替代的'。"]]],

  [87, "Traditional Festivals Around the World", "文化", 1,
"Traditional festivals serve as vibrant expressions of cultural identity, bringing communities together to celebrate shared heritage, values, and beliefs. From the colorful Holi festival in India to the solemn Day of the Dead in Mexico, these celebrations offer windows into the rich diversity of human culture.\n\nChinese New Year, also known as the Spring Festival, is the most important traditional holiday in China. Celebrated by over a billion people worldwide, it marks the beginning of the lunar new year with family reunions, feasting, and the giving of red envelopes containing money. Dragon and lion dances, fireworks, and elaborate decorations in red and gold characterize the festivities.\n\nDiwali, the Festival of Lights, is celebrated by Hindus, Sikhs, and Jains around the world. The five-day festival symbolizes the victory of light over darkness and good over evil. Families light oil lamps and candles, create colorful floor designs called rangoli, exchange gifts, and enjoy elaborate feasts.\n\nCarnival in Brazil is one of the world's largest festivals, attracting millions of participants and spectators. The festival features elaborate parades with floats and costumed performers, samba music and dancing, and street parties throughout the country. While commercialization has transformed many traditional festivals, they continue to play vital roles in preserving cultural traditions and strengthening community bonds.",
"传统节日是文化认同的生动表达，将社区聚集在一起庆祝共同的遗产、价值观和信仰。从印度色彩缤纷的胡里节到墨西哥庄严的亡灵节，这些庆祝活动提供了了解人类文化丰富多样性的窗口。\n\n中国新年（春节）是中国最重要的传统节日。全球超过十亿人庆祝，它标志着农历新年的开始，以家庭团聚、盛宴和发红包为特色。\n\n排灯节是印度教徒、锡克教徒和耆那教徒庆祝的灯火节。这个五天节日象征着光明战胜黑暗、善良战胜邪恶。\n\n巴西狂欢节是世界上最大的节日之一，吸引了数百万参与者和观众。虽然商业化改变了许多传统节日，但它们在保存文化传统和加强社区联系方面继续发挥着重要作用。",
338,
[["What does Chinese New Year mark?","The end of summer","The beginning of the lunar new year","The harvest season","The rainy season","B","文章指出春节标志着农历新年的开始。"],["What does Diwali symbolize?","The beginning of war","The victory of light over darkness and good over evil","The end of the year","The monsoon season","B","文章指出排灯节象征着光明战胜黑暗、善良战胜邪恶。"],["What is rangoli?","A type of food","Colorful floor designs created during Diwali","A musical instrument","A dance style","B","文章指出rangoli是在排灯节期间创建的彩色地板设计。"],["What role do traditional festivals continue to play?","Only generating profit","Preserving cultural traditions and strengthening community bonds","Only attracting tourists","Creating competition between countries","B","文章指出传统节日在保存文化传统和加强社区联系方面继续发挥重要作用。"]]],

  [88, "The Influence of Pop Culture", "文化", 2,
"Popular culture, encompassing music, film, television, fashion, and social media trends, exerts a powerful influence on societies worldwide. In the age of digital communication, pop culture spreads more rapidly and broadly than ever before, shaping attitudes, behaviors, and identities across diverse populations.\n\nThe global reach of American pop culture is particularly notable. Hollywood films, American music, and US-based social media platforms dominate global entertainment. This cultural influence, sometimes called soft power, can shape international perceptions and attitudes. However, the dominance of American pop culture has also sparked concerns about cultural imperialism.\n\nKorean pop culture, known as the Hallyu wave, has emerged as a significant counterforce. K-pop music, Korean dramas, and Korean beauty products have gained massive international followings. The success of groups like BTS and television shows like Squid Game demonstrates that cultural influence flows in multiple directions.\n\nSocial media has democratized cultural production, allowing individuals and small groups to create and distribute content that can reach global audiences. TikTok challenges, YouTube creators, and Instagram influencers can shape trends as effectively as traditional media companies. However, the rapid pace of cultural trends on social media can also promote superficial engagement and fleeting attention spans. Understanding the influence of pop culture is essential for navigating the modern cultural landscape.",
"流行文化对全球社会产生了强大影响。在数字通信时代，流行文化比以往更快更广泛地传播，塑造着不同人群的态度、行为和身份。\n\n美国流行文化的全球影响力特别显著。好莱坞电影、美国音乐和社交媒体平台主导着全球娱乐。然而，美国流行文化的主导地位也引发了文化帝国主义的担忧。\n\n韩国流行文化（韩流）已作为重要的反向力量出现。K-pop音乐、韩剧和韩国美容产品获得了大量国际追随者。BTS组合和《鱿鱼游戏》等电视剧的成功表明文化影响是双向流动的。\n\n社交媒体使文化生产民主化，允许个人和小群体创建和分发可以到达全球受众的内容。然而，社交媒体上文化趋势的快速节奏也可能促进肤浅的参与。",
338,
[["What is soft power?","Military strength","Cultural influence that shapes international perceptions and attitudes","Economic sanctions","Political treaties","B","文章指出软实力是塑造国际观念和态度的文化影响。"],["What is the Hallyu wave?","A type of natural disaster","The global spread of Korean pop culture","A political movement","A technology trend","B","文章指出韩流是韩国流行文化的全球传播。"],["How has social media changed cultural production?","Made it more expensive","Democratized it, allowing individuals to create and distribute content globally","Eliminated all cultural production","Made it controlled only by governments","B","文章指出社交媒体使文化生产民主化。"],["The word 'imperialism' most likely means:","Equal cultural exchange","Domination of one culture over others","Cultural preservation","Cultural celebration","B","'imperialism'意为'帝国主义'，此处指文化上的支配和主导。"]]],

  [89, "Food Culture and Identity", "文化", 1,
"Food is far more than mere sustenance; it is a powerful expression of cultural identity and a vehicle for transmitting traditions across generations. The dishes we prepare, the ingredients we value, and the rituals surrounding meals all reflect deeply held cultural beliefs and practices.\n\nCuisine varies dramatically across cultures, shaped by geography, climate, history, and religion. Mediterranean diets emphasize olive oil, fresh vegetables, and seafood, reflecting the region's climate and coastal geography. Asian cuisines feature rice as a staple, with diverse preparations reflecting local traditions and available ingredients. These culinary traditions carry centuries of accumulated knowledge about nutrition, agriculture, and food preservation.\n\nFood also serves as a bridge between cultures. Immigration and globalization have introduced cuisines to new audiences, with dishes like sushi, tacos, and curry becoming global favorites. Fusion cuisine combines elements from different culinary traditions, creating new flavors and cross-cultural understanding.\n\nHowever, traditional food cultures face threats from industrialization and globalization. The standardization of food through fast food chains and processed products can erode local culinary traditions. Food deserts, areas with limited access to fresh and nutritious food, disproportionately affect low-income communities. Preserving food heritage while adapting to modern lifestyles is a challenge that communities around the world are navigating.",
"食物远不止是简单的维持生存；它是文化认同的有力表达，也是跨代传承传统的载体。我们准备的菜肴、我们看重的食材和围绕餐食的仪式都反映了深层的文化信仰和实践。\n\n菜系在不同文化间差异巨大，受地理、气候、历史和宗教影响。地中海饮食强调橄榄油、新鲜蔬菜和海鲜。亚洲菜系以大米为主食。\n\n食物也是文化之间的桥梁。移民和全球化将各种菜系介绍给新的受众。融合菜结合了不同烹饪传统的元素，创造了新的风味和跨文化理解。\n\n然而，传统饮食文化面临工业化和全球化的威胁。快餐连锁和加工产品对食物的标准化可能侵蚀当地的烹饪传统。",
338,
[["What shapes cuisine according to the passage?","Only personal preference","Geography, climate, history, and religion","Only available restaurants","Only cooking shows","B","文章指出菜系受地理、气候、历史和宗教影响。"],["What is fusion cuisine?","Only fast food","Cuisine combining elements from different culinary traditions","Only traditional dishes","Frozen food","B","文章指出融合菜结合了不同烹饪传统的元素。"],["What threatens traditional food cultures?","More home cooking","Industrialization, fast food chains, and processed products","Too many farmers","Excessive food variety","B","文章指出快餐连锁和加工产品对食物的标准化威胁传统饮食文化。"],["The word 'sustenance' most likely means:","Entertainment","Food and drink needed to sustain life","Clothing","Shelter","B","'sustenance'意为'维持生命的食物和饮料'。"]]],

  [90, "Language and Cultural Identity", "文化", 2,
"Language is far more than a tool for communication; it is a fundamental expression of cultural identity and a repository of accumulated knowledge and worldviews. The words we use, the metaphors we employ, and the stories we tell all reflect deeply held cultural values and perspectives.\n\nLinguistic diversity is remarkable. With approximately 7,000 languages spoken worldwide, each represents a unique way of categorizing and understanding the world. Some languages have dozens of words for snow or rice, reflecting the importance of these elements in their cultures. Others have grammatical structures that encode different relationships between people, time, and space.\n\nThe loss of a language represents an irretrievable loss of human knowledge and cultural heritage. When a language dies, the traditional ecological knowledge, oral histories, and cultural practices encoded in that language are also at risk. Indigenous languages often contain detailed knowledge about local ecosystems, medicinal plants, and sustainable resource management.\n\nLanguage revitalization efforts are underway around the world. Programs that teach endangered languages to new generations, develop written forms for previously oral languages, and create digital resources are helping to preserve linguistic diversity. The Maori language revival in New Zealand is often cited as a successful model, where immersive education programs and media broadcasting have significantly increased the number of speakers.",
"语言远不止是交流工具；它是文化认同的基本表达，也是积累的知识和世界观的宝库。\n\n语言多样性是显著的。全球约7000种语言，每种都代表了分类和理解世界的独特方式。一些语言有几十个描述雪或米的词，反映了这些元素在其文化中的重要性。\n\n语言的消失代表着人类知识和文化遗产的不可挽回的损失。原住民语言通常包含关于当地生态系统、药用植物和可持续资源管理的详细知识。\n\n世界各地正在进行语言复兴努力。向新一代教授濒危语言、为以前口头语言发展书面形式以及创建数字资源的计划正在帮助保护语言多样性。新西兰毛利语的复兴常被引为成功模式。",
338,
[["How many languages are spoken worldwide?","About 1,000","About 3,000","About 7,000","About 10,000","C","文章指出全球约7000种语言。"],["What is at risk when a language dies?","Nothing important","Traditional ecological knowledge, oral histories, and cultural practices","Only grammar rules","Only the alphabet","B","文章指出语言消失时，传统生态知识、口述历史和文化实践也面临风险。"],["What is often cited as a successful model of language revival?","Latin revival","Maori language revival in New Zealand","English revival in America","French revival in Canada","B","文章指出新西兰毛利语复兴常被引为成功模式。"],["The word 'irretrievable' most likely means:","Easy to recover","Impossible to recover or get back","Not important","Temporary","B","'irretrievable'意为'不可挽回的、无法恢复的'。"]]],

  [91, "The Impact of Social Media on Culture", "文化", 2,
"Social media has become a dominant force in shaping contemporary culture. Platforms like Instagram, TikTok, and Twitter influence everything from fashion and music to political discourse and social movements. With billions of users worldwide, social media platforms have become the primary channels through which many people experience and participate in culture.\n\nOne significant impact of social media is the acceleration of cultural trends. Ideas, memes, and fashions can spread globally within hours, creating viral phenomena that capture public attention briefly before being replaced by the next trend. This rapid cycle can promote novelty over depth and discourage sustained engagement with cultural content.\n\nSocial media has also transformed cultural gatekeeping. In the past, cultural production was largely controlled by traditional media companies, publishers, and critics. Today, anyone with a smartphone can create and distribute cultural content, potentially reaching millions. This democratization has given voice to previously marginalized perspectives and enabled niche communities to flourish.\n\nHowever, social media's impact on culture is not uniformly positive. Algorithm-driven content curation can create filter bubbles that reinforce existing beliefs and limit exposure to diverse perspectives. The pressure to present an idealized version of life online can promote inauthenticity and anxiety. Cyberbullying and online harassment represent darker aspects of social media culture. Navigating the cultural landscape of social media requires critical awareness of both its possibilities and its pitfalls.",
"社交媒体已成为塑造当代文化的主导力量。Instagram、TikTok和Twitter等平台影响着从时尚和音乐到政治话语和社会运动的一切。\n\n社交媒体的一个重要影响是文化趋势的加速。想法、表情包和时尚可以在几小时内全球传播。这种快速循环可能促进新奇而牺牲深度。\n\n社交媒体还改变了文化守门。过去，文化生产主要由传统媒体公司、出版商和评论家控制。今天，任何拥有智能手机的人都可以创建和分发文化内容。\n\n然而，社交媒体对文化的影响并非全是积极的。算法驱动的内容策划可能创造过滤气泡，强化现有信念并限制接触多元观点。",
338,
[["What is one significant impact of social media on culture?","Slowing down cultural trends","Acceleration of cultural trends through rapid global spread","Eliminating all cultural trends","Only preserving traditional culture","B","文章指出社交媒体加速了文化趋势的全球传播。"],["What has social media done to cultural gatekeeping?","Made it stricter","Democratized it, allowing anyone to create and distribute cultural content","Eliminated all gatekeeping","Made it controlled only by governments","B","文章指出社交媒体使文化守门民主化，允许任何人创建和分发文化内容。"],["What are filter bubbles?","Physical water filters","Algorithm-driven content curation that reinforces existing beliefs","Internet firewalls","Anti-virus software","B","文章指出过滤气泡是算法驱动的内容策划，强化现有信念并限制接触多元观点。"],["The word 'inauthenticity' most likely means:","Genuineness","The quality of being fake or not genuine","Honesty","Creativity","B","'inauthenticity'意为'不真实、虚假'。"]]],

  [92, "Cultural Exchange Through Education", "文化", 1,
"International education serves as a powerful vehicle for cultural exchange and mutual understanding. When students study abroad, attend international schools, or participate in cross-cultural programs, they gain firsthand experience of different ways of life that can transform their perspectives and career trajectories.\n\nStudy abroad programs allow students to immerse themselves in a foreign culture, developing language skills and cultural competence that cannot be acquired through textbooks alone. Students learn to navigate unfamiliar social norms, adapt to different educational systems, and appreciate diverse viewpoints. These experiences foster empathy and reduce stereotypes.\n\nInternational schools and universities create microcosms of global diversity. Classrooms that include students from multiple countries provide opportunities for peer-to-peer cultural learning. Group projects and social interactions naturally expose students to different communication styles, problem-solving approaches, and cultural values.\n\nVirtual exchange programs have expanded access to cross-cultural education. Through video conferencing, collaborative online projects, and digital platforms, students who cannot travel abroad can still engage with peers from different cultures. While virtual exchanges cannot fully replicate the experience of living in another country, they provide valuable opportunities for dialogue and collaboration across borders. As technology continues to advance, the potential for virtual cultural exchange will only grow.",
"国际教育是文化交流和相互理解的有力载体。当学生留学、就读国际学校或参与跨文化项目时，他们获得了可以改变视角和职业轨迹的不同生活方式的第一手经验。\n\n留学项目允许学生沉浸在外语文化中，发展仅靠教科书无法获得的语言技能和文化能力。这些经验培养了同理心并减少了刻板印象。\n\n国际学校和大学创造了全球多样性的缩影。来自多个国家的学生组成的课堂提供了同伴间文化学习的机会。\n\n虚拟交流项目扩大了跨文化教育的可及性。通过视频会议、协作在线项目和数字平台，无法出国的学生仍然可以与来自不同文化的同龄人交流。",
338,
[["What do study abroad programs allow students to develop?","Only academic knowledge","Language skills and cultural competence through immersion","Only cooking skills","Only athletic abilities","B","文章指出留学项目允许学生通过沉浸式学习发展语言技能和文化能力。"],["What do international classrooms provide?","Only lectures","Opportunities for peer-to-peer cultural learning","Only exams","Only sports activities","B","文章指出来自多个国家的学生组成的课堂提供了同伴间文化学习的机会。"],["What have virtual exchange programs done?","Replaced all physical exchanges","Expanded access to cross-cultural education for those who cannot travel","Eliminated cultural exchange","Made travel unnecessary for everyone","B","文章指出虚拟交流项目为无法出国的学生扩大了跨文化教育的可及性。"],["The word 'microcosms' most likely means:","Large universes","Small representations of a larger system","Microscopic organisms","Computer programs","B","'microcosms'意为'缩影'，指更大系统的小型代表性。"]]],

  [93, "Music as Cultural Expression", "文化", 1,
"Music is a universal language that transcends borders while simultaneously expressing the unique characteristics of individual cultures. Throughout history, music has served as a powerful means of cultural expression, storytelling, and community bonding.\n\nTraditional music reflects the values, experiences, and environments of the cultures that produce it. African drumming traditions encode complex social messages and historical narratives. Indian classical music follows intricate melodic frameworks called ragas that are associated with different moods, seasons, and times of day. Indigenous Australian music uses the didgeridoo to recreate the sounds of the natural landscape.\n\nThe globalization of music has created both opportunities and challenges. Digital streaming platforms have made music from around the world accessible to global audiences. Artists can reach listeners in distant countries without the mediation of traditional record labels. Cross-cultural collaborations between musicians from different traditions have produced innovative and exciting new genres.\n\nHowever, the commercialization of music can also lead to cultural appropriation, where elements of marginalized cultures are adopted by dominant cultures without proper acknowledgment or respect. The line between appreciation and appropriation is often contested. Supporting fair compensation for traditional musicians and respecting the cultural significance of musical traditions are important principles for ethical musical exchange.",
"音乐是一种超越边界的通用语言，同时表达着个体文化的独特特征。纵观历史，音乐一直是文化表达、讲故事和社区联系的有力手段。\n\n传统音乐反映了产生它的文化的价值观、经验和环境。非洲鼓乐传统编码了复杂的社会信息和历史叙事。印度古典音乐遵循与不同情绪、季节和时间段相关的复杂旋律框架。\n\n音乐的全球化创造了机遇和挑战。数字流媒体平台使全球观众可以接触到世界各地的音乐。来自不同传统的音乐家之间的跨文化合作产生了创新和令人兴奋的新流派。\n\n然而，音乐的商业化也可能导致文化挪用。欣赏和挪用之间的界限经常存在争议。",
338,
[["What do African drumming traditions encode?","Only entertainment","Complex social messages and historical narratives","Only rhythm patterns","Only dance instructions","B","文章指出非洲鼓乐传统编码了复杂的社会信息和历史叙事。"],["What are ragas in Indian classical music?","Musical instruments","Intricate melodic frameworks associated with different moods and times","Dance styles","Singing techniques","B","文章指出raga是与不同情绪、季节和时间段相关的复杂旋律框架。"],["What is cultural appropriation in music?","Fair collaboration between cultures","Adopting elements of marginalized cultures without acknowledgment or respect","Playing music from other countries","Learning a new instrument","B","文章指出文化挪用是在没有适当承认或尊重的情况下采纳边缘化文化的元素。"],["The word 'mediation' most likely means:","Direct access","Intermediation or the act of mediating between parties","Elimination","Celebration","B","'mediation'意为'中介、调解'。"]]],

  [94, "Architecture and Cultural Identity", "文化", 2,
"Architecture is one of the most visible and enduring expressions of cultural identity. The buildings and urban spaces that people create reflect their values, beliefs, social structures, and relationship with the natural environment. From ancient temples to modern skyscrapers, architecture tells the story of human civilization.\n\nTraditional architecture is deeply connected to local conditions. Materials are sourced from the immediate environment, designs respond to local climate, and spatial arrangements reflect social customs. The courtyard houses of China, the yurts of Central Asian nomads, and the stilt houses of Southeast Asia all represent sophisticated adaptations to specific cultural and environmental contexts.\n\nThe spread of international architectural styles has created concerns about the loss of regional identity. Glass-and-steel skyscrapers now dominate skylines around the world, with little reference to local building traditions or cultural contexts. Critics argue that this architectural homogenization diminishes the distinctive character of cities and erodes cultural identity.\n\nContemporary architects are increasingly seeking to integrate traditional design principles with modern technologies and materials. This approach, sometimes called critical regionalism, creates buildings that are both contemporary and culturally rooted. Projects that incorporate local materials, respond to climate conditions, and respect cultural practices demonstrate that modern architecture need not come at the expense of cultural identity.",
"建筑是文化认同最可见和最持久的表达之一。人们创造的建筑和城市空间反映了他们的价值观、信仰、社会结构和与自然环境的关系。\n\n传统建筑与当地条件深度关联。材料来自近处环境，设计响应当地气候，空间布局反映社会习俗。中国的四合院、中亚游牧民族的蒙古包和东南亚的吊脚楼都代表了对特定文化和环境背景的精密适应。\n\n国际建筑风格的传播引发了对地区身份丧失的担忧。钢化玻璃摩天大楼现在主导着世界各地的天际线，很少参考当地建筑传统或文化背景。\n\n当代建筑师越来越多地寻求将传统设计原则与现代技术和材料整合。",
338,
[["What does traditional architecture reflect?","Only aesthetic preferences","Values, beliefs, social structures, and relationship with environment","Only available budget","Only building technology","B","文章指出传统建筑反映了价值观、信仰、社会结构和与环境的关系。"],["What are courtyard houses of China an example of?","Modern architecture","Sophisticated adaptations to specific cultural and environmental contexts","Only decorative buildings","Temporary shelters","B","文章指出中国的四合院代表了对特定文化和环境背景的精密适应。"],["What concern does the spread of international architectural styles create?","Lower construction costs","Loss of regional identity and architectural homogenization","More job opportunities","Better climate control","B","文章指出国际建筑风格的传播引发了对地区身份丧失和建筑同质化的担忧。"],["What is critical regionalism?","Rejecting all modern technology","Integrating traditional design principles with modern technologies and materials","Only using ancient building methods","Ignoring local culture","B","文章指出批判性地方主义将传统设计原则与现代技术和材料整合。"]]],

  [95, "Cultural Taboos and Social Norms", "文化", 2,
"Cultural taboos and social norms vary dramatically across societies, reflecting deeply held values and beliefs about what is appropriate, acceptable, and sacred. Understanding these differences is essential for effective cross-cultural communication and avoiding unintentional offense.\n\nFood taboos are among the most well-known cultural restrictions. Hindus do not eat beef, Muslims and Jews avoid pork, and many Buddhists are vegetarian. These restrictions are rooted in religious beliefs and carry deep spiritual significance. Offering inappropriate food to someone from a different culture can be deeply offensive.\n\nGesture and body language taboos also vary significantly. The thumbs-up sign, commonly used to indicate approval in Western countries, is considered offensive in some Middle Eastern cultures. Pointing with the index finger is rude in many Asian cultures, where people indicate direction with their whole hand. Personal space expectations differ greatly, with some cultures favoring close physical proximity and others requiring more distance.\n\nGift-giving customs are another area rich with cultural variation. In many Asian cultures, gifts should be given and received with both hands, and opening a gift immediately in front of the giver can be considered impolite. In some Western contexts, opening the gift immediately is expected as a sign of appreciation. Learning about cultural norms before visiting or working with people from different backgrounds demonstrates respect and facilitates smoother interactions.",
"文化禁忌和社会规范在不同社会间差异巨大，反映了对什么是适当、可接受和神圣的深层价值观和信仰。\n\n食物禁忌是最著名的文化限制之一。印度教徒不吃牛肉，穆斯林和犹太人避免猪肉，许多佛教徒是素食者。这些限制根植于宗教信仰。\n\n手势和肢体语言禁忌也差异显著。竖大拇指在西方表示赞许，但在一些中东文化中被认为是冒犯的。用食指指向在许多亚洲文化中是不礼貌的。\n\n送礼习俗也是文化差异丰富的领域。在许多亚洲文化中，礼物应该用双手给予和接收，在送礼者面前立即打开礼物可能被认为是不礼貌的。在访问或与不同背景的人合作之前了解文化规范表示尊重。",
338,
[["What are food taboos rooted in?","Only personal preference","Religious beliefs with deep spiritual significance","Only health concerns","Only economic factors","B","文章指出食物禁忌根植于宗教信仰并具有深层精神意义。"],["What gesture is considered offensive in some Middle Eastern cultures?","Bowing","The thumbs-up sign","Shaking hands","Waving","B","文章指出竖大拇指在一些中东文化中被认为是冒犯的。"],["How should gifts be given in many Asian cultures?","With one hand only","With both hands","By throwing them","By mail only","B","文章指出在许多亚洲文化中，礼物应该用双手给予和接收。"],["The word 'taboos' most likely means:","Popular trends","Cultural prohibitions against certain actions or behaviors","Types of food","Musical instruments","B","'taboos'意为'禁忌'，指对某些行为或做法的文化禁止。"]]],

  [96, "The Evolution of Writing Systems", "文化", 2,
"The development of writing systems represents one of humanity's most significant cultural achievements. From the earliest cuneiform tablets to modern digital text, the ability to record and transmit information across time and space has fundamentally shaped human civilization.\n\nThe earliest known writing systems emerged independently in several regions around 5,000 years ago. Sumerian cuneiform in Mesopotamia, Egyptian hieroglyphics, and Chinese characters all developed as ways to record commercial transactions, religious texts, and administrative records. These early scripts required years of study to master, creating a class of scribes who held significant social power.\n\nThe invention of the alphabet was a revolutionary simplification. Instead of using separate symbols for each word or concept, alphabetic systems use a small set of symbols to represent individual sounds. The Phoenician alphabet, developed around 1050 BCE, is the ancestor of most modern alphabets, including Latin, Arabic, and Cyrillic.\n\nChinese characters represent a different approach, using logographic symbols where each character represents a word or morpheme. While more complex to learn, this system allows readers who speak different dialects to share a common written language. Today, writing systems continue to evolve. Digital communication has introduced emojis, abbreviations, and new forms of written expression that reflect contemporary culture and communication needs.",
"书写系统的发展是人类最重要的文化成就之一。从最早的楔形文字到现代数字文本，跨越时空记录和传输信息的能力从根本上塑造了人类文明。\n\n已知最早的书写系统约在5000年前在几个地区独立出现。苏美尔楔形文字、埃及象形文字和中国汉字都是为了记录商业交易、宗教文本和行政记录而发展起来的。\n\n字母的发明是一次革命性的简化。字母系统使用少量符号来表示单个声音，而不是每个词或概念使用单独的符号。腓尼基字母约在公元前1050年发展，是大多数现代字母的祖先。\n\n汉字代表了一种不同的方法，使用表意符号，每个字符代表一个词或语素。虽然学习起来更复杂，但这个系统允许说不同方言的读者共享共同的书面语言。",
338,
[["When did the earliest known writing systems emerge?","About 1,000 years ago","About 5,000 years ago","About 10,000 years ago","About 500 years ago","B","文章指出已知最早的书写系统约在5000年前出现。"],["What was revolutionary about the alphabet?","It used more symbols","It used a small set of symbols to represent individual sounds instead of whole words","It was harder to learn","It could only be used for poetry","B","文章指出字母系统使用少量符号表示单个声音，而不是使用单独的符号代表每个词。"],["When was the Phoenician alphabet developed?","Around 500 BCE","Around 1050 BCE","Around 2000 BCE","Around 100 CE","B","文章指出腓尼基字母约在公元前1050年发展。"],["What advantage do Chinese characters have?","They are easy to learn","They allow readers who speak different dialects to share a common written language","They use very few characters","They are only used in China","B","文章指出汉字系统允许说不同方言的读者共享共同的书面语言。"]]],

  [97, "Traditional Medicine and Modern Science", "文化", 2,
"Traditional medicine systems, developed over thousands of years across different cultures, continue to play important roles in healthcare worldwide. From Traditional Chinese Medicine to Ayurveda in India, these systems offer approaches to health and healing that differ significantly from Western biomedicine.\n\nTraditional Chinese Medicine is based on the concept of qi, the vital energy that flows through the body along pathways called meridians. Practices such as acupuncture, herbal medicine, and tai chi aim to restore the balance and flow of qi. While these concepts may seem unscientific to Western eyes, acupuncture has been endorsed by the World Health Organization for treating dozens of conditions.\n\nAyurveda, the traditional medical system of India, emphasizes the balance between mind, body, and spirit. It uses dietary modifications, herbal remedies, yoga, and meditation to maintain health and treat illness. Many Ayurvedic practices have been validated by modern research, including the anti-inflammatory properties of turmeric.\n\nThe integration of traditional and modern medicine presents both opportunities and challenges. Traditional knowledge can provide valuable leads for drug development, as demonstrated by artemisinin, a malaria treatment derived from a herb used in Chinese traditional medicine that earned its discoverer a Nobel Prize. However, ensuring the safety and efficacy of traditional remedies through rigorous scientific testing remains important. Respecting traditional knowledge while maintaining scientific standards is an ongoing challenge in global healthcare.",
"传统医学体系在不同文化中发展了数千年，继续在全球医疗保健中发挥重要作用。从中医到印度阿育吠陀，这些体系提供了与西方生物医学显著不同的健康和治疗方法。\n\n中医基于气的概念，即沿着经络流经身体的生命能量。针灸、草药和太极等实践旨在恢复气的平衡和流动。虽然这些概念在西方看来可能不科学，但针灸已被世界卫生组织认可用于治疗数十种疾病。\n\n阿育吠陀强调心灵、身体和精神之间的平衡。许多阿育吠陀实践已得到现代研究的验证。\n\n传统和现代医学的整合既带来机遇也带来挑战。青蒿素是一种从中草药中提取的疟疾治疗药物，为其发现者赢得了诺贝尔奖。然而，通过严格的科学测试确保传统疗法的安全性和有效性仍然很重要。",
338,
[["What is qi in Traditional Chinese Medicine?","A type of food","Vital energy that flows through the body along meridians","A medical instrument","A type of exercise","B","文章指出中医中气是沿着经络流经身体的生命能量。"],["What has the WHO endorsed acupuncture for?","Only pain relief","Treating dozens of conditions","Only stress reduction","Only cosmetic purposes","B","文章指出针灸已被世界卫生组织认可用于治疗数十种疾病。"],["What malaria treatment was derived from Chinese traditional medicine?","Aspirin","Artemisinin","Penicillin","Quinine","B","文章指出青蒿素是一种从中草药中提取的疟疾治疗药物。"],["The word 'efficacy' most likely means:","Cost","Effectiveness in producing a desired result","Popularity","Taste","B","'efficacy'意为'功效、有效性'。"]]],

  [98, "Cultural Differences in Communication", "文化", 2,
"Communication styles vary significantly across cultures, and misunderstandings arising from these differences can create barriers in both personal and professional relationships. Understanding cultural variations in communication is essential for effective interaction in our increasingly interconnected world.\n\nHigh-context cultures, such as those in East Asia and the Middle East, rely heavily on implicit communication, nonverbal cues, and shared understanding. In these cultures, what is not said can be as important as what is said. Direct confrontation and explicit disagreement may be avoided to preserve harmony and face.\n\nLow-context cultures, such as those in Northern Europe and North America, prioritize explicit and direct verbal communication. Messages are expected to be clear and unambiguous, and directness is valued as honesty. People from low-context cultures may find high-context communication vague or evasive, while those from high-context cultures may perceive direct communication as rude or insensitive.\n\nSilence also carries different meanings across cultures. In Japanese culture, silence can indicate respect, thoughtfulness, or disagreement without confrontation. In many Western cultures, silence in conversation may be perceived as awkward or indicative of a problem. The concept of saving face is crucial in many Asian cultures, where preserving one's own and others' dignity takes precedence over blunt honesty. Developing cultural communication competence requires awareness of these differences and the flexibility to adapt one's communication style accordingly.",
"沟通方式在不同文化间差异显著，由这些差异产生的误解可能在个人和职业关系中造成障碍。\n\n高语境文化，如东亚和中东的文化，严重依赖隐含沟通、非语言线索和共同理解。在这些文化中，没说的话可能和说了的话一样重要。\n\n低语境文化，如北欧和北美文化，优先考虑明确直接的口头沟通。来自低语境文化的人可能觉得高语境沟通模糊或回避，而来自高语境文化的人可能认为直接沟通粗鲁或不敏感。\n\n沉默在不同文化中也带有不同含义。在日本文化中，沉默可以表示尊重、深思或不同意而不对抗。面子观念在许多亚洲文化中至关重要。培养文化沟通能力需要意识到这些差异。",
338,
[["What do high-context cultures rely on?","Only written communication","Implicit communication, nonverbal cues, and shared understanding","Only verbal communication","Only technology","B","文章指出高语境文化严重依赖隐含沟通、非语言线索和共同理解。"],["What do low-context cultures prioritize?","Silence","Explicit and direct verbal communication","Indirect hints","Nonverbal cues only","B","文章指出低语境文化优先考虑明确直接的口头沟通。"],["What can silence indicate in Japanese culture?","Only agreement","Respect, thoughtfulness, or disagreement without confrontation","Only ignorance","Only anger","B","文章指出在日本文化中沉默可以表示尊重、深思或不对抗的不同意。"],["What is the concept of 'saving face'?","Avoiding physical danger","Preserving one's own and others' dignity, taking precedence over blunt honesty","Saving money","Physical protection","B","文章指出面子观念是保持自己和他人的尊严，优先于直白的诚实。"]]],

  [99, "Cultural Impact of the Olympic Games", "文化", 1,
"The Olympic Games represent one of the world's most significant cultural events, bringing together athletes and spectators from virtually every nation. Beyond athletic competition, the Olympics serve as a platform for cultural exchange, national identity expression, and international diplomacy.\n\nThe opening ceremony of the Olympic Games has become a showcase for host nations to present their cultural heritage to a global audience. From the elaborate displays of Beijing in 2008 to the celebration of British history in London in 2012, these ceremonies combine artistic performance, technology, and cultural storytelling on a grand scale.\n\nThe Olympic Village creates a unique multicultural environment where athletes from diverse backgrounds live and interact. Many athletes describe the experience of meeting competitors from other countries as one of the most meaningful aspects of their Olympic experience. Cultural exchange programs, joint training facilities, and social events facilitate these interactions.\n\nHowever, the Olympics are not without cultural controversies. The choice of host cities can spark debates about human rights and cultural policies. The commercialization of the Games has drawn criticism for prioritizing corporate interests over cultural values. The cost of hosting the Olympics can strain public resources that might otherwise support cultural programs. Despite these challenges, the Olympic movement continues to promote its founding ideal of using sport to build a better and more peaceful world.",
"奥运会代表世界上最重要的文化活动之一，汇聚了来自几乎所有国家的运动员和观众。超越体育竞赛，奥运会是文化交流、国家认同表达和国际外交的平台。\n\n奥运会开幕式已成为主办国向全球观众展示其文化遗产的平台。从2008年北京精心设计的展示到2012年伦敦对英国历史的庆祝，这些仪式在宏大尺度上结合了艺术表演、技术和文化叙事。\n\n奥运村创造了一个独特的多元文化环境。许多运动员描述与来自其他国家的竞争对手的会面是奥运会经历中最有意义的方面之一。\n\n然而，奥运会并非没有文化争议。主办城市的选择可能引发关于人权和文化政策的辩论。奥运会的商业化因将企业利益置于文化价值之上而受到批评。",
338,
[["What do the Olympics serve as beyond athletic competition?","Only a business venture","A platform for cultural exchange, national identity expression, and diplomacy","Only a tourism event","Only a military exercise","B","文章指出奥运会超越体育竞赛，是文化交流、国家认同表达和国际外交的平台。"],["What has the Olympic opening ceremony become?","A simple athletic event","A showcase for host nations to present their cultural heritage to a global audience","A political debate","A concert only","B","文章指出开幕式已成为主办国向全球观众展示其文化遗产的平台。"],["What unique environment does the Olympic Village create?","A shopping mall","A multicultural environment where athletes from diverse backgrounds interact","A military base","A research facility","B","文章指出奥运村创造了来自不同背景的运动员互动的多元文化环境。"],["What criticism of Olympic commercialization is mentioned?","Not enough advertising","Prioritizing corporate interests over cultural values","Too many athletes","Not enough sports","B","文章指出奥运会的商业化因将企业利益置于文化价值之上而受到批评。"]]],

  [100, "World Heritage Sites", "文化", 2,
"World Heritage Sites, designated by the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization, represent places of outstanding cultural or natural importance to the common heritage of humanity. Since the World Heritage Convention was adopted in 1972, over 1,100 sites in 167 countries have been inscribed on the World Heritage List.\n\nCultural World Heritage Sites include monuments, groups of buildings, and archaeological sites of outstanding universal value. From the Great Wall of China to the Pyramids of Egypt, these sites represent the pinnacle of human creative achievement and provide tangible connections to our shared past.\n\nNatural World Heritage Sites feature natural features, geological formations, and ecosystems of exceptional beauty or scientific importance. The Great Barrier Reef, the Galapagos Islands, and Yellowstone National Park are among the most famous natural sites. These areas protect irreplaceable natural heritage for future generations.\n\nHowever, World Heritage Sites face numerous threats. Climate change, mass tourism, armed conflict, urbanization, and inadequate management all endanger these precious places. UNESCO maintains a List of World Heritage in Danger to highlight sites facing imminent threats and mobilize international assistance. The destruction of sites like the Buddhas of Bamiyan in Afghanistan and the ancient city of Palmyra in Syria has demonstrated the vulnerability of cultural heritage in times of conflict. Preserving World Heritage Sites requires sustained international cooperation and resources.",
"世界遗产地由联合国教科文组织指定，代表对人类共同遗产具有突出文化或自然重要性的地方。自1972年世界遗产公约通过以来，167个国家的1100多个地点已被列入世界遗产名录。\n\n文化世界遗产地包括具有突出普遍价值的纪念碑、建筑群和考古遗址。从中国长城到埃及金字塔，这些遗址代表了人类创造性成就的巅峰。\n\n自然世界遗产地以具有特殊美感或科学重要性的自然特征、地质构造和生态系统为特色。大堡礁、加拉帕戈斯群岛和黄石国家公园是最著名的自然遗址。\n\n然而，世界遗产地面临许多威胁。气候变化、大规模旅游、武装冲突、城市化和管理不足都危及这些珍贵的地方。教科文组织维护濒危世界遗产名录以突出面临紧迫威胁的地点。",
338,
[["When was the World Heritage Convention adopted?","1962","1972","1982","1992","B","文章指出世界遗产公约于1972年通过。"],["How many sites have been inscribed on the World Heritage List?","Over 100","Over 500","Over 1,100","Over 5,000","C","文章指出超过1100个地点已被列入世界遗产名录。"],["What threats do World Heritage Sites face?","Only natural disasters","Climate change, mass tourism, armed conflict, urbanization, and inadequate management","Only tourism","Only weather","B","文章指出世界遗产地面临气候变化、大规模旅游、武装冲突、城市化和管理不足等威胁。"],["The word 'inscribed' most likely means:","Erased","Written or recorded on a list","Destroyed","Forgotten","B","'inscribed'意为'铭刻、列入'。"]]],

  [101, "The Role of Museums in Cultural Preservation", "文化", 1,
"Museums play a vital role in preserving and presenting cultural heritage to the public. From art museums and history museums to science centers and cultural institutions, these organizations serve as guardians of human knowledge and creativity.\n\nThe traditional role of museums as custodians of objects has evolved significantly. Modern museums see themselves not merely as storehouses of artifacts but as active educators and community resources. Interactive exhibits, educational programs, and digital archives make cultural heritage accessible to diverse audiences.\n\nThe debate over cultural repatriation has become increasingly prominent. Many museums in Western countries hold artifacts that were acquired during colonial periods, and source countries are demanding their return. The British Museum's holding of the Parthenon Marbles and the debate over the Benin Bronzes highlight the complex ethical and legal issues surrounding cultural property.\n\nDigital technology is transforming how museums operate. Virtual tours allow people worldwide to explore collections without traveling. Three-dimensional scanning and printing can create accurate replicas of fragile objects, reducing the need to display originals. Online databases make collection information available to researchers globally. While digital access cannot replace the experience of seeing objects in person, it significantly expands the reach and impact of museums. As museums continue to evolve, they must balance preservation with accessibility, tradition with innovation, and institutional authority with community engagement.",
"博物馆在保存和向公众展示文化遗产方面发挥着重要作用。从艺术博物馆和历史博物馆到科学中心和文化机构，这些组织是人类知识和创造力的守护者。\n\n博物馆作为物品保管者的传统角色已经显著演变。现代博物馆将自身视为积极的教育者和社区资源。\n\n关于文化归还的辩论日益突出。许多西方国家的博物馆持有在殖民时期获得的文物，来源国要求归还。大英博物馆持有的帕台农神庙大理石雕和关于贝宁青铜器的辩论突显了围绕文化财产的复杂伦理和法律问题。\n\n数字技术正在改变博物馆的运营方式。虚拟参观允许全球人们无需旅行即可探索收藏品。",
338,
[["How has the role of museums evolved?","They only store objects now","From mere storehouses of artifacts to active educators and community resources","They have become less important","They only focus on art","B","文章指出博物馆从单纯的文物储存库演变为积极的教育者和社区资源。"],["What is cultural repatriation?","Sending tourists to other countries","The return of cultural artifacts to their countries of origin","Building new museums","Selling artifacts to collectors","B","文章指出文化归还是将文化文物归还给其来源国。"],["What does the British Museum hold that is controversial?","The Mona Lisa","The Parthenon Marbles","The Great Wall","The Pyramids","B","文章指出大英博物馆持有帕台农神庙大理石雕引发了争议。"],["The word 'repatriation' most likely means:","Selling to the highest bidder","Returning something to its country of origin","Destroying artifacts","Lending to other museums","B","'repatriation'意为'归还、遣返'，此处指将文物归还给来源国。"]]],

  [102, "Cultural Traditions in the Digital Age", "文化", 2,
"The digital age has brought both unprecedented opportunities and challenges for the preservation and transmission of cultural traditions. Technology offers powerful new tools for documenting, sharing, and revitalizing cultural practices, but it also poses threats to the authenticity and context of traditional knowledge.\n\nDigital documentation technologies enable the recording of cultural practices in unprecedented detail. High-resolution video can capture traditional crafts and performances for future generations. Audio recordings preserve endangered languages and oral traditions. Online archives make cultural materials accessible to diaspora communities and researchers worldwide.\n\nSocial media platforms have become important spaces for cultural expression and community building. Indigenous communities use social media to share their traditions, organize cultural events, and connect with diaspora members. However, the public nature of social media can also expose sacred or sensitive cultural practices to inappropriate audiences.\n\nThe question of who controls digital representations of cultural traditions is complex. When cultural materials are digitized and shared online, they can be taken out of their proper context and used in ways that disrespect their cultural significance. Issues of intellectual property and cultural sovereignty become particularly challenging in digital environments. Developing ethical guidelines for the digital representation of cultural traditions is an ongoing concern for communities and institutions worldwide.",
"数字时代为文化传统的保存和传承带来了前所未有的机遇和挑战。技术提供了记录、分享和复兴文化实践的强大新工具，但也对传统知识的真实性和语境构成了威胁。\n\n数字文档技术使以前所未有的细节记录文化实践成为可能。高分辨率视频可以捕捉传统工艺和表演。音频记录保存濒危语言和口头传统。在线档案使文化材料可供全球散居社区和研究人员访问。\n\n社交媒体平台已成为文化表达和社区建设的重要空间。原住民社区使用社交媒体分享他们的传统。\n\n谁控制文化传统的数字表现形式是一个复杂的问题。当文化材料被数字化并在线分享时，它们可能脱离适当的语境并以不尊重其文化意义的方式使用。",
338,
[["What opportunity does digital technology offer for cultural traditions?","Only entertainment","Powerful new tools for documenting, sharing, and revitalizing cultural practices","Only social media","Only commercial opportunities","B","文章指出数字技术为记录、分享和复兴文化实践提供了强大的新工具。"],["What is a challenge of social media for cultural traditions?","It is too expensive","Sacred or sensitive cultural practices can be exposed to inappropriate audiences","It does not work well","Only young people use it","B","文章指出社交媒体的公共性质可能使神圣或敏感的文化实践暴露给不适当的受众。"],["What happens when cultural materials are shared online?","They become more valuable","They can be taken out of context and used in ways that disrespect their significance","They are always protected","They disappear","B","文章指出文化材料在线分享时可能脱离语境并被以不尊重的方式使用。"],["The word 'sovereignty' most likely means:","Poverty","Supreme authority or control","Technology","Celebration","B","'sovereignty'意为'主权、最高权力'。"]]],

  [103, "The Cultural Significance of Sports", "文化", 1,
"Sports occupy a central place in cultures around the world, serving as more than mere physical contests. They embody cultural values, reinforce social bonds, and provide powerful narratives of identity and belonging. Understanding the cultural significance of sports provides insight into the societies that embrace them.\n\nDifferent sports reflect different cultural priorities. American football emphasizes strategy, specialization, and territorial conquest, reflecting certain aspects of American culture. Soccer, the world's most popular sport, emphasizes fluid teamwork and universal accessibility. Martial arts in Asian cultures embody philosophical principles of discipline, respect, and harmony between mind and body.\n\nSports can serve as powerful unifying forces within societies. Major sporting events like the World Cup and the Olympics bring entire nations together in shared enthusiasm and pride. The success of national teams can boost collective morale and provide moments of joy that transcend social divisions.\n\nHowever, sports can also reflect and reinforce social inequalities. Gender disparities in pay, media coverage, and opportunities persist across most sports. Racial dynamics in sports mirror broader societal issues of discrimination and representation. The commercialization of professional sports has created vast inequalities between elite athletes and the vast majority of participants. Despite these challenges, sports continue to play a vital role in cultural expression and social cohesion worldwide.",
"体育在世界各地的文化中占据着中心位置，远不止是简单的体育竞赛。它们体现了文化价值观，加强了社会联系，提供了关于认同和归属的强大叙事。\n\n不同的体育项目反映了不同的文化优先事项。美式足球强调战略、专业化和领地征服，反映了美国文化的某些方面。足球是世界上最受欢迎的运动，强调流畅的团队合作和普遍可及性。亚洲文化中的武术体现了自律、尊重和身心和谐的哲学原则。\n\n体育可以在社会内部发挥强大的统一力量。世界杯和奥运会等重大体育赛事使整个国家团结在一起。\n\n然而，体育也可以反映和加强社会不平等。大多数体育项目中，薪酬、媒体报道和机会方面的性别差距持续存在。",
338,
[["What do martial arts in Asian cultures embody?","Only fighting skills","Philosophical principles of discipline, respect, and harmony","Only physical fitness","Only competition","B","文章指出亚洲文化中的武术体现了自律、尊重和身心和谐的哲学原则。"],["What is the world's most popular sport?","American football","Soccer","Cricket","Basketball","B","文章指出足球是世界上最受欢迎的运动。"],["What can major sporting events do?","Only generate revenue","Bring entire nations together in shared enthusiasm and pride","Only create conflict","Only benefit athletes","B","文章指出世界杯和奥运会等重大体育赛事使整个国家团结在一起。"],["What social inequality in sports is mentioned?","Only age differences","Gender disparities in pay, media coverage, and opportunities","Only skill differences","Only regional differences","B","文章指出大多数体育项目中存在薪酬、媒体报道和机会方面的性别差距。"]]],

  [104, "Cultural Adaptation of Immigrants", "文化", 2,
"When people migrate to a new country, they face the complex challenge of adapting to a different culture while maintaining elements of their own cultural identity. This process of cultural adaptation, sometimes called acculturation, varies significantly depending on individual circumstances and the receptiveness of the host society.\n\nResearch has identified several patterns of cultural adaptation. Some immigrants adopt the culture of their new country while abandoning their heritage culture, a process known as assimilation. Others maintain their original culture while minimizing contact with the host culture, a pattern called separation. A third approach, integration, involves maintaining one's heritage culture while also participating in the larger society. Studies generally find that integration leads to the best psychological and social outcomes.\n\nThe experience of second-generation immigrants, children born to immigrant parents in the host country, is particularly complex. They often navigate between two cultural worlds, facing expectations from both their heritage community and the mainstream society. This bicultural experience can be both enriching and challenging.\n\nHost societies play a crucial role in the adaptation process. Countries with policies that support multiculturalism and provide language training, recognition of foreign qualifications, and anti-discrimination protections tend to facilitate more successful integration. Negative attitudes toward immigrants, whether expressed through discrimination or exclusionary policies, can create significant barriers to adaptation and contribute to social isolation and mental health problems.",
"当人们移民到一个新国家时，他们面临着适应不同文化同时保持自己文化认同要素的复杂挑战。这种文化适应过程因个人情况和接收社会的接受程度而有很大差异。\n\n研究已经确定了几种文化适应模式。一些移民在接受新国家文化的同时放弃其传统文化，这被称为同化。另一些人维持原有文化同时尽量减少与主流文化的接触，这被称为分离。第三种方法是整合，即保持传统文化同时也参与更大的社会。研究通常发现整合带来最好的心理和社会结果。\n\n第二代移民的经历特别复杂。他们通常在两种文化世界之间航行。\n\n接收社会在适应过程中起着关键作用。支持多元文化主义并提供语言培训、承认外国资格和反歧视保护的国家往往促进更成功的整合。",
338,
[["What is assimilation in the context of cultural adaptation?","Maintaining both cultures equally","Adopting the host culture while abandoning the heritage culture","Rejecting all cultures","Only eating local food","B","文章指出同化是接受新国家文化的同时放弃传统文化。"],["What adaptation pattern leads to the best outcomes according to studies?","Assimilation","Separation","Integration","Marginalization","C","文章指出研究通常发现整合带来最好的心理和社会结果。"],["What makes the experience of second-generation immigrants complex?","They have no cultural identity","They navigate between two cultural worlds with expectations from both","They only identify with the host culture","They only identify with their heritage culture","B","文章指出第二代移民在两种文化世界之间航行，面临传统文化社区和主流社会的期望。"],["What do countries with successful integration policies provide?","Only financial aid","Language training, recognition of foreign qualifications, and anti-discrimination protections","Only housing","Only citizenship","B","文章指出成功整合的国家提供语言培训、承认外国资格和反歧视保护。"]]]
];
